AFTER being on the run for more than a month, a murder suspect has finally been bust.The man (22), who is suspected of killing a cop in Bluff, Durban will appear in the Durban Magistrates Court today, facing charges of business robbery and murder.KZN police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said the suspect was bust in Umlazi on Friday. &ldquo;We are grateful to residents for helping the cops find the suspect,&rdquo; said Zwane. The suspect and his friend (30), who is currently in jail, allegedly shot and killed Constable Thomas Kwela (37) of Brighton Beach cop shop.It happened during a robbery in February.Daily Sun reported that Kwela and his colleagues had responded to a robbery when robbers shot at them. The first suspect was arrested shortly after the incident.&ldquo;He appeared in the Durban Magistrates Court and his case was postponed to 9 June,&rdquo; said Zwane.He said the second suspect might be linked to other business robberies in KZN and other provinces.&ldquo;On Thursday, a warrant of arrest against the suspect was issued, as well as a sketch of the wanted man&rsquo;s face,&rdquo; said Zwane.